{"type":"message","id":"e8108de9","parentId":"a11e7dbe","timestamp":"2026-03-25T15:01:29.275Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_web_search_xXw6vP5fSmuYShxHYQY6","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Jokowi\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1667,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b18adec917ed7572\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nJoko Widodo | Biography & Facts - Britannica\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b18adec917ed7572\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.britannica.com/biography/Joko-Widodo\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f888eb1f333b60d2\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nJoko Widodo The presidency of Joko Widodo left a mixed legacy in Indonesia but is well regarded for effectively eradicating extreme poverty. Joko Widodo was born and raised in Surakarta, a city in the centre of Java northeast of Yogyakarta, Indonesia. Prior to becoming Indonesia’s president, Joko Widodo worked for a state-owned pulp mill in the Aceh region of northern Sumatra and later established his own furniture factory in Surakarta. **Joko Widodo** (born June 21, 1961, Surakarta, Central Java, Indonesia) is an Indonesian businessman, politician, and government official who served as governor of Jakarta (2012–14) and as president of Indonesia (2014–24). Joko Widodo, commonly called Jokowi, who attracted international attention with his populist style of campaigning and his anticorruption platform, became the first Indonesian president who did not have a military background or belong to one of the country’s prominent political families. Joko WidodoJoko Widodo (left) with former Indonesian president Megawati Sukarnoputri (right) in Jakarta, 2012.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f888eb1f333b60d2\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.84948516\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c0073e35e2c91544\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nJoko Widodo - Wikipedia\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c0073e35e2c91544\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joko_Widodo\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"14a979ceab04a695\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n| **7th President of Indonesia**   ---   Pre-presidency  * Mayor of Surakarta   + BST   + Esemka * Governor of Jakarta   + LRT   + MRT   ---   Presidency  * Cabinets   + First \\\"Working Cabinet (2014–2019)\\\")   + Second * Jokowi Effect * Bali Nine * High-speed rail * Trans-Sumatra * New capital * Sea Toll Program * Omnibus Law * Solo Gang * Nickel downstreaming * Major protests   + 212 Movement   + 2019 election   + Papua   + KPK law   + 2022 student protests   + Omnibus law   + Local election law   ---   Summits  * ASEAN Summit * G20   + 2014   + 2015   + 2016   + 2017   + 2019   + 2020   + 2021   + 2022   + 2023 * APEC   + 2014   + 2015   + 2016   + 2017   + 2018   + 2020   + 2021   + 2022   + 2023 * Presidential trips   ---   Elections  * 2005 mayoral * 2010 mayoral * 2012 gubernatorial * 2014 presidential   + campaign   + inauguration * 2019 presidential   + campaign   + inauguration   ---   Family  * Parents   + Widjiatno   + Sudjiatmi * Iriana (spouse and first lady) * Siblings   + Iit Sriyantini   + Titik Relawati   + Idayati * Children   + Gibran   + Kahiyang   + Kaesang * Other relatives   + Selvi   + Bobby   + Erina   + Anwar |.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"14a979ceab04a695\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.7368747\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ef59110570d534e8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe Tragedy of Joko Widodo | Council on Foreign Relations\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ef59110570d534e8\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.cfr.org/articles/tragedy-joko-widodo\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7b0938c31a483735\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe fact that Jokowi even allied with Prabowo, a man with a history of disdain for Indonesia’s democracy, little secret of his desire to reduce limitations on presidential power, and a long history of alleged abuses during the Suharto era, shows how far Jokowi has fallen. This version of Jokowi starkly contrasts his early image as a supposedly self-made, new Indonesian figure who would reform politics and clean house of politicians like Prabowo. After initially promising he had no interest in building a political family dynasty, a sharp contrast from most other Indonesian politicians, Jokowi built one of the country’s most robust and possibly longest-lasting dynasties. On foreign policy, never a major interest of Jokowi’s, the president focused on aid and investment into Indonesia but shied away from major crises in the region, including political backsliding in places like Cambodia, let alone the outright coup and civil war in Myanmar. Whether he can maintain all those levers remains to be seen, as the new president, Prabowo Subianto, may eventually move to reduce Jokowi’s power.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"7b0938c31a483735\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.60805947\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1d880a9b4be455c0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFormer Indonesian President Jokowi faces storm of lawsuits six ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1d880a9b4be455c0\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://asianews.network/former-indonesian-president-jokowi-faces-storm-of-lawsuits-six-months-after-stepping-down/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6c58ea4dd7a6d7fc\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFormer president Joko “Jokowi” Widodo has been the target of a barrage of lawsuits, which analysts say underscores the accumulated disapproval over his\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6c58ea4dd7a6d7fc\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.5689194\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dceb33871fc36c27\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe Post-Presidency Storm Around Joko Widodo - Asia Sentinel\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dceb33871fc36c27\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.asiasentinel.com/p/post-presidency-storm-around-joko-widodo\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8d093389f39232b1\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMost recently, Indonesia’s Corruption Eradication Commission (KPK) opened an investigation into alleged corruption in the construction of the high-speed train Whoosh, a project launched and completed under Jokowi’s administration. During his two terms as president, Jokowi consolidated power by bringing as many political parties as possible into his coalition — including the Great Indonesia Movement Party (Partai Gerindra), led by Prabowo Subianto, now the country’s president and twice Jokowi’s rival in the 2014 and 2019 elections. “It was President Jokowi’s decision.”. Budi also clarified that Projo no longer stands for “Pro Jokowi,” but rather represents the “people.” The former minister of cooperatives expressed hope of joining Prabowo’s Gerindra Party, rather than Jokowi’s allied PSI. Nailul Huda, an economist at the Center of Economic and Law Studies (Celios), said it would not be surprising if Prabowo decides to discontinue some of Jokowi’s National Strategic Projects.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"8d093389f39232b1\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.4765072\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Jokowi","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1667,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b18adec917ed7572\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nJoko Widodo | Biography & Facts - Britannica\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b18adec917ed7572\">>>","url":"https://www.britannica.com/biography/Joko-Widodo","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f888eb1f333b60d2\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nJoko Widodo The presidency of Joko Widodo left a mixed legacy in Indonesia but is well regarded for effectively eradicating extreme poverty. Joko Widodo was born and raised in Surakarta, a city in the centre of Java northeast of Yogyakarta, Indonesia. Prior to becoming Indonesia’s president, Joko Widodo worked for a state-owned pulp mill in the Aceh region of northern Sumatra and later established his own furniture factory in Surakarta. **Joko Widodo** (born June 21, 1961, Surakarta, Central Java, Indonesia) is an Indonesian businessman, politician, and government official who served as governor of Jakarta (2012–14) and as president of Indonesia (2014–24). Joko Widodo, commonly called Jokowi, who attracted international attention with his populist style of campaigning and his anticorruption platform, became the first Indonesian president who did not have a military background or belong to one of the country’s prominent political families. Joko WidodoJoko Widodo (left) with former Indonesian president Megawati Sukarnoputri (right) in Jakarta, 2012.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f888eb1f333b60d2\">>>","score":0.84948516},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c0073e35e2c91544\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nJoko Widodo - Wikipedia\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c0073e35e2c91544\">>>","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joko_Widodo","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"14a979ceab04a695\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n| **7th President of Indonesia**   ---   Pre-presidency  * Mayor of Surakarta   + BST   + Esemka * Governor of Jakarta   + LRT   + MRT   ---   Presidency  * Cabinets   + First \"Working Cabinet (2014–2019)\")   + Second * Jokowi Effect * Bali Nine * High-speed rail * Trans-Sumatra * New capital * Sea Toll Program * Omnibus Law * Solo Gang * Nickel downstreaming * Major protests   + 212 Movement   + 2019 election   + Papua   + KPK law   + 2022 student protests   + Omnibus law   + Local election law   ---   Summits  * ASEAN Summit * G20   + 2014   + 2015   + 2016   + 2017   + 2019   + 2020   + 2021   + 2022   + 2023 * APEC   + 2014   + 2015   + 2016   + 2017   + 2018   + 2020   + 2021   + 2022   + 2023 * Presidential trips   ---   Elections  * 2005 mayoral * 2010 mayoral * 2012 gubernatorial * 2014 presidential   + campaign   + inauguration * 2019 presidential   + campaign   + inauguration   ---   Family  * Parents   + Widjiatno   + Sudjiatmi * Iriana (spouse and first lady) * Siblings   + Iit Sriyantini   + Titik Relawati   + Idayati * Children   + Gibran   + Kahiyang   + Kaesang * Other relatives   + Selvi   + Bobby   + Erina   + Anwar |.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"14a979ceab04a695\">>>","score":0.7368747},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ef59110570d534e8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe Tragedy of Joko Widodo | Council on Foreign Relations\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ef59110570d534e8\">>>","url":"https://www.cfr.org/articles/tragedy-joko-widodo","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7b0938c31a483735\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe fact that Jokowi even allied with Prabowo, a man with a history of disdain for Indonesia’s democracy, little secret of his desire to reduce limitations on presidential power, and a long history of alleged abuses during the Suharto era, shows how far Jokowi has fallen. This version of Jokowi starkly contrasts his early image as a supposedly self-made, new Indonesian figure who would reform politics and clean house of politicians like Prabowo. After initially promising he had no interest in building a political family dynasty, a sharp contrast from most other Indonesian politicians, Jokowi built one of the country’s most robust and possibly longest-lasting dynasties. On foreign policy, never a major interest of Jokowi’s, the president focused on aid and investment into Indonesia but shied away from major crises in the region, including political backsliding in places like Cambodia, let alone the outright coup and civil war in Myanmar. Whether he can maintain all those levers remains to be seen, as the new president, Prabowo Subianto, may eventually move to reduce Jokowi’s power.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7b0938c31a483735\">>>","score":0.60805947},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1d880a9b4be455c0\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFormer Indonesian President Jokowi faces storm of lawsuits six ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1d880a9b4be455c0\">>>","url":"https://asianews.network/former-indonesian-president-jokowi-faces-storm-of-lawsuits-six-months-after-stepping-down/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6c58ea4dd7a6d7fc\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFormer president Joko “Jokowi” Widodo has been the target of a barrage of lawsuits, which analysts say underscores the accumulated disapproval over his\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6c58ea4dd7a6d7fc\">>>","score":0.5689194},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dceb33871fc36c27\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe Post-Presidency Storm Around Joko Widodo - Asia Sentinel\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dceb33871fc36c27\">>>","url":"https://www.asiasentinel.com/p/post-presidency-storm-around-joko-widodo","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"8d093389f39232b1\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMost recently, Indonesia’s Corruption Eradication Commission (KPK) opened an investigation into alleged corruption in the construction of the high-speed train Whoosh, a project launched and completed under Jokowi’s administration. During his two terms as president, Jokowi consolidated power by bringing as many political parties as possible into his coalition — including the Great Indonesia Movement Party (Partai Gerindra), led by Prabowo Subianto, now the country’s president and twice Jokowi’s rival in the 2014 and 2019 elections. “It was President Jokowi’s decision.”. Budi also clarified that Projo no longer stands for “Pro Jokowi,” but rather represents the “people.” The former minister of cooperatives expressed hope of joining Prabowo’s Gerindra Party, rather than Jokowi’s allied PSI. Nailul Huda, an economist at the Center of Economic and Law Studies (Celios), said it would not be surprising if Prabowo decides to discontinue some of Jokowi’s National Strategic Projects.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"8d093389f39232b1\">>>","score":0.4765072}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774450889269}}
{"type":"message","id":"bab7c92d","parentId":"e8108de9","timestamp":"2026-03-25T15:01:32.324Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nSaya sudah mencari informasi tentang Jokowi. Berikut beberapa hasil yang saya temukan:\n\n*   **Britannica:** Memberikan biografi Joko Widodo, termasuk latar belakang, karir sebagai gubernur Jakarta, dan masa kepresidenannya dari 2014-2024. Ia dikenal sebagai presiden pertama tanpa latar belakang militer atau dari keluarga politik terkemuka, serta pendekatan populis dan anti-korupsinya.\n*   **Wikipedia:** Merangkum masa jabatannya sebagai Presiden ke-7 Indonesia, termasuk berbagai kabinet, program-program besar seperti kereta cepat dan pemindahan ibu kota, serta informasi pemilu dan keluarga.\n*   **Council on Foreign Relations:** Membahas warisan Joko Widodo, termasuk aliansinya dengan Prabowo Subianto, pembangunan dinasti politik, dan fokus pada Bantuan Luar Negeri serta investasi.\n*   **Asia Sentinel:** Melaporkan tentang tuntutan hukum yang dihadapi Jokowi setelah masa jabatannya, serta dinamika politik terkait Prabowo Subianto dan proyek-proyek strategis nasional.\n\nApakah ada informasi spesifik tentang Jokowi yang ingin Anda ketahui lebih lanjut?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":2788,"output":237,"cacheRead":14537,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17562,"cost":{"input":-2788,"output":-237,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-3025}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774450889277,"responseId":"gen-1774450889-eAku6MOQ2R3qQUqPtDCz"}}
