{"type":"message","id":"14e38111","parentId":"59625660","timestamp":"2026-03-25T15:57:22.978Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Exploring user request**\n\nThe user asked to use OpenClaw to open a specific URL, but our tools don't support a direct browser launch. Instead, I can simulate a browser experience by using the web_fetch tool to grab the content or provide the URL. So, I’ll likely fetch the content in text mode to show what the user wants. This way, I can display the page content or summarize it for them!**Fetching content for the user**\n\nI need to be aware that the content might be long, so I can fetch up to 20,000 characters. I’ll use the \"text\" extract mode for plain text. After fetching, I can summarize key details like the Bitcoin price from CoinGecko. I'll call the web_fetch function with the appropriate URL and parameters to get the data. Since the user prefers Indonesian, I'll keep my response in that language and clearly explain what I can provide.**Using web_fetch tool**\n\nI need to keep in mind that the web_fetch tool will return raw markdown or text content, which means I’ll need to extract the important parts afterward. So, let’s go ahead and call the tool to fetch the necessary data. From there, I can focus on pulling out the key information that the user is looking for! This should give us what we need to provide a helpful response.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1m6XeGvlgtU6qreEmGQAdqO3","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/bitcoin","extractMode":"text","maxChars":100000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":15649,"output":949,"cacheRead":2048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18646,"cost":{"input":-15649,"output":-949,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-16598}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774454232405,"responseId":"gen-1774454232-X8sugYzKa7JtGhwy58Jz"}}
